# PHP Coding Rules

# 1. Use PSR-12 coding style
# 2. Use strict types
# 3. Use namespaces and autoloading
# 4. Prefer dependency injection over global state
# 5. Use exceptions for error handling
# 6. Write unit tests for your code
# 7. Use meaningful variable and function names
# 8. Keep functions small and focused
# 9. Use comments to explain complex logic
# 10. Avoid using deprecated features 